<!-- HERO -->
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-left">
    <div class="eyebrow">IncomeArchitect™ Modeler</div>
    <h1>The retirement plan<br>you can see <em>before</em><br>you commit to it.</h1>
    <p class="hero-lead">A proprietary planning tool used exclusively by IPP advisor partners. It projects your complete retirement income picture — every source, every year, every risk — and shows you exactly what changes when the IncomeArc™ architecture is in place.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/structure-review.html" class="btn-primary">Begin Your StructureReview™</a>
      <a href="#how-it-works" class="btn-secondary">See How It Works</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-right">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="IncomeArchitect™ Modeler — Architecture ON with all stress scenarios active"/>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- STATS -->
<div class="stats">
  <div class="stats-inner">
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-val">34</div><div class="stat-lbl">Projection years modeled</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-val">1,000</div><div class="stat-lbl">Monte Carlo trials per scenario</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-val">6+</div><div class="stat-lbl">Income sources tracked</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-val">Real-time</div><div class="stat-lbl">Recalculates on every input change</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- CAPABILITIES -->
<section id="how-it-works" style="background:var(--navy2);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="s-eyebrow">What It Does</div>
    <h2 class="s-h">A complete retirement picture,<br>built <em>while you watch.</em></h2>
    <p class="s-sub">The IncomeArchitect™ Modeler is a live planning environment — not a static report. Every input change recalculates the entire projection instantly, so advisors and clients can explore every scenario together in real time.</p>
    <div class="cap-grid">
      <div class="cap-card">
        <div class="cap-num">01</div>
        <div class="cap-title">Income Projection Arc</div>
        <div class="cap-desc">Year-by-year income waterfall showing exactly where retirement income comes from at every age — Social Security, pension, RMDs, Roth distributions, ETA policy loans, and portfolio draws — stacked against an inflation-adjusted expense line. Surplus and gap years are visible at a glance.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cap-card">
        <div class="cap-num">02</div>
        <div class="cap-title">Architecture ON/OFF Toggle</div>
        <div class="cap-desc">The most powerful feature. Toggle Architecture ON and the projection rebuilds around the IncomeArc™ four-layer system. RMD exposure shifts. Tax liability moves. The confidence score changes — sometimes dramatically. The difference between two paths becomes visible and undeniable.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cap-card">
        <div class="cap-num">03</div>
        <div class="cap-title">Monte Carlo Confidence Score</div>
        <div class="cap-desc">1,000 randomized return trials run against your actual income structure, withdrawal rates, and guaranteed income streams. The result: a single probability score representing how likely the plan is to fully fund expenses to the plan-to age. Honest, not optimistic.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cap-card">
        <div class="cap-num">04</div>
        <div class="cap-title">Sequence of Returns Risk</div>
        <div class="cap-desc">Toggle SORR to apply a stress-tested return sequence in the first five retirement years — showing exactly what a bad early market does to your specific plan. The confidence score and chart update simultaneously to reflect the real probability of survival under adverse conditions.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cap-card">
        <div class="cap-num">05</div>
        <div class="cap-title">Health Event Modeling</div>
        <div class="cap-desc">Model a long-term care event for you, your spouse, or both — including the full tax gross-up cost of funding care from a pre-tax IRA. Show the uninsured portfolio spike against the Architecture-protected plan side by side. The cost of inaction becomes quantified, not theoretical.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cap-card">
        <div class="cap-num">06</div>
        <div class="cap-title">Tax, IRMAA &amp; Full Debit Breakdown</div>
        <div class="cap-desc">Federal tax, state tax, IRMAA Medicare surcharges, and LTC gross-up costs tracked year by year across five dedicated views. The IRS co-ownership of your qualified plan isn't abstract — it's a line item, growing larger every year, until someone addresses it.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FEATURE 1: Base case -->
<div class="feat">
  <div class="feat-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="feat-lbl">The Starting Point</div>
      <h3 class="feat-h">Your status quo,<br><em>rendered honestly.</em></h3>
      <p class="feat-body">Before exploring what's possible, the IncomeArchitect™ Modeler establishes exactly where you stand. Every income source layered by year. Every tax and IRMAA cost visible. The trajectory of your qualified plan balance — and the growing RMD exposure embedded in it.</p>
      <p class="feat-body">Most people have never seen their retirement income presented this way. The chart makes the picture clear before a single recommendation is made.</p>
      <ul class="feat-pts">
        <li>Social Security, pension, and portfolio draws shown by source and tax character</li>
        <li>Inflation-adjusted expense line overlaid against income — gap years visible immediately</li>
        <li>IRMAA Medicare surcharges tracked in a dedicated sub-panel year by year</li>
        <li>89% Monte Carlo confidence score — calculated against 1,000 return scenarios</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="screen-wrap">
      <div class="screen-frame">
        <div class="screen-bar">
          <div class="dot" style="background:#C47A7A"></div>
          <div class="dot" style="background:#C8A030"></div>
          <div class="dot" style="background:#7BAF84"></div>
          <div class="screen-url">IncomeArchitect™ Modeler — Status Quo</div>
        </div>
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="IncomeArchitect™ Modeler — Base Case / Status Quo"/>
      </div>
      <div class="badge-float">Base Case — Architecture OFF</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- FEATURE 2: Health Events -->
<div class="feat dark">
  <div class="feat-inner rev">
    <div>
      <div class="feat-lbl">Health Event Modeling</div>
      <h3 class="feat-h">Show the real cost<br>of being <em>uninsured.</em></h3>
      <p class="feat-body">Most clients have never seen what a long-term care event actually costs their portfolio — not in today's dollars, but inflated at 4% to the event age, drawn from a pre-tax IRA with the full tax gross-up applied.</p>
      <p class="feat-body">Toggle Health Events ON and the model shows both the uninsured scenario — with the expense spike and confidence score drop — and what the Architecture-protected plan looks like with a Layer 2 policy covering the same event. The difference is immediate and visible.</p>
      <ul class="feat-pts">
        <li>Primary and spouse care events modeled independently at any age</li>
        <li>Care cost inflated at 4% annually to the event age — real future dollars, not today's</li>
        <li>Uninsured expense spike vs. Architecture-protected flat line shown simultaneously</li>
        <li>Confidence score drops from 89% to 73% — the probability cost of no plan</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="screen-wrap">
      <div class="screen-frame">
        <div class="screen-bar">
          <div class="dot" style="background:#C47A7A"></div>
          <div class="dot" style="background:#C8A030"></div>
          <div class="dot" style="background:#7BAF84"></div>
          <div class="screen-url">IncomeArchitect™ Modeler — Health Events ON</div>
        </div>
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="IncomeArchitect™ Modeler — Health Events ON"/>
      </div>
      <div class="badge-float">HC Event 78–80 &amp; Spouse 86–89</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- FEATURE 3: SORR / Perfect Storm -->
<div class="feat">
  <div class="feat-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="feat-lbl">Sequence of Returns Risk</div>
      <h3 class="feat-h">The perfect storm.<br><em>Before it happens.</em></h3>
      <p class="feat-body">Add SORR to Health Events and the model applies a stress-tested return sequence in the first five retirement years — combined with both care events active and no Architecture protection. This is the scenario most financial plans are never stress-tested against.</p>
      <p class="feat-body">In this scenario, the portfolio depletes at age 86 — 12 years before plan end. Income from guaranteed sources continues, but all portfolio draws cease. The confidence score falls to 6%. The plan is At Risk.</p>
      <ul class="feat-pts">
        <li>SORR schedule: -18%, +4%, -14%, +5%, -10% in years one through five</li>
        <li>Health events for both spouses layer on top of the early return stress</li>
        <li>Portfolio depletion warning — age 86, 12 years before plan end</li>
